 one’s life experiences or topical social issues, as well as how to create appealing characters and bring them to life. Their insights, production tales, and fresh, practical, and proven advice make this book ideal for film lovers, screenwriting students, and filmmakers and screenwriters seeking inspiration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aMotion picture authorship. 0aMotion picture producers and directorsvInterviews. 0aScreenwritersvInterviews. 0aScreenwriters--Interviews. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Screenwriting.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Paul Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aApatow, Judd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranco, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranco, James.1 aJosephson, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorgan, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorgan, Barbara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPerez, Maya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerez, Maya, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRodríguez, Álvaro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSumner, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWittliff, Bill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/31090840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477311943423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477311943/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SS